1
00:00:00,630 --> 00:00:02,240
<i>Previously on Dracula...</i>

2
00:00:02,320 --> 00:00:04,750
It'll be my honor to host your engagement party.

3
00:00:05,460 --> 00:00:06,780
Things will never be the same.

4
00:00:07,110 --> 00:00:09,190
You are to be married, and that is that.

5
00:00:09,190 --> 00:00:10,630
She is Ilona.

6
00:00:10,630 --> 00:00:13,680
You must never again mention Mina Murray's resemblance to my wife.

7
00:00:13,980 --> 00:00:17,900
I need your blood to create a serum so you are able to conquer daylight.

8
00:00:18,210 --> 00:00:20,580
I want you to find out everything about this General Shaw.

9
00:00:20,580 --> 00:00:22,700
He's a powerful ally of my competitors.

10
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:27,590
Vera Markham can tell you all you need to know about Shaw.

11
00:00:27,590 --> 00:00:28,060
Yes?

12
00:00:28,060 --> 00:00:30,420
You wish to employ my services

13
00:00:30,420 --> 00:00:33,790
in order to get Mr. Renfield to answer one question.

14
00:01:01,330 --> 00:01:04,330
Mr. Grayson. What are you doing here?

15
00:01:04,330 --> 00:01:07,580
I know I shouldn't be here, but there's no time.

16
00:01:07,690 --> 00:01:08,780
Time for what?

17
00:01:10,780 --> 00:01:13,560
No. You must leave, immediately, or... I'll go.

18
00:01:14,130 --> 00:01:15,150
I promise.

19
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:20,480
But I must tell you, you're making a mistake.

20
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:22,360
A terrible mistake.

21
00:01:23,060 --> 00:01:24,980
- What do you mean? - Harker.

22
00:01:25,780 --> 00:01:28,080
He'll never be able to make you happy, and you know it.

23
00:01:28,820 --> 00:01:29,920
How dare you.

24
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:32,950
Now is not the time for lies, Mina.

25
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:36,690
You know it's the truth. If it isn't, say it.

26
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:39,360
Look me in the eyes and say it,

27
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:41,230
- and I'll go. - No, no, no.

28
00:01:41,230 --> 00:01:45,340
- I... I love... I love Jonathan, and no other,

29
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:47,140
and he will be my husband.

30
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:28,520
Of all the days to lie-in.

31
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:34,990
Don't you know we have a million things to do before tonight?

32
00:02:36,950 --> 00:02:39,150
- It's still on? - Of course it's still on!

33
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:44,230
- Unless you've reconsidered. - No. No. No, of course not.

34
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:49,040
Well then, for goodness' sake, get up, darling.

35
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:52,090
You mustn't waste another second of this momentous day.

36
00:02:52,890 --> 00:02:53,550
Yours is going to be

37
00:02:53,550 --> 00:02:56,570
the most spectacular engagement party London has ever seen.

38
00:03:03,530 --> 00:03:05,600
Be careful. That's very fragile.

39
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,190
Come and meet your first test subject.

40
00:03:10,730 --> 00:03:12,710
Place it in line with the door, please.

41
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:17,550
And no obstruction that may cast a shadow!

42
00:03:27,650 --> 00:03:29,040
I wouldn't get too close, Professor.

43
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:34,200
I think you'll find her suitable, if not exactly agreeable.

44
00:03:39,180 --> 00:03:41,410
There are many technical challenges,

45
00:03:41,410 --> 00:03:43,890
but I believe we will surmount them, given time.

46
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:45,560
Time is a luxury we do not have.

47
00:03:49,090 --> 00:03:51,010
I must walk in sunlight soon.

48
00:03:51,010 --> 00:03:52,690
People are getting suspicious.

49
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:54,620
Do you understand?

50
00:03:57,050 --> 00:03:58,770
By the way, where's Renfield?

51
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:00,650
He was meant to accompany the lab equipment.

52
00:04:00,650 --> 00:04:04,640
Renfield was nowhere to be found. I had to do it myself.

53
00:04:16,930 --> 00:04:18,520
Mr. Renfield.

54
00:04:19,060 --> 00:04:21,960
We are about to embark on a journey, you and I.

55
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:24,990
It begins with a single question,

56
00:04:24,990 --> 00:04:28,010
and it ends with your answer to that question.

57
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:38,150
I want you to remember that, so I will say it again.

58
00:04:39,410 --> 00:04:42,170
It ends with your answer.

59
00:04:42,970 --> 00:04:46,060
So you see, no matter how helpless you may feel,

60
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:50,870
no matter how lengthy, debasing, and disagreeable

61
00:04:50,870 --> 00:04:52,280
the journey may prove,

62
00:04:53,450 --> 00:04:56,010
ultimately, you are in control.

63
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,790
Let's get started, shall we?

64
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:09,400
Though I take great pride in my profession,

65
00:05:10,030 --> 00:05:11,240
it has become...

66
00:05:14,010 --> 00:05:16,150
tedious of late.

67
00:05:20,030 --> 00:05:21,370
There are, after all,

68
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:25,310
only so many variations on a theme one can play.

69
00:05:25,310 --> 00:05:26,370
Release me.

70
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:36,640
Each client is unique, of course.

71
00:05:37,690 --> 00:05:39,020
The methods vary,

72
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:42,720
but the result is inevitably the same.

73
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,690
I'm warning you,

74
00:05:45,550 --> 00:05:47,830
there will be repercussions.

75
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:54,030
I often think, "Perhaps this time, Janina.

76
00:05:54,790 --> 00:05:56,580
"This time, for once,

77
00:05:57,020 --> 00:05:59,480
"the client will dispense with all the bluster and defiance

78
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:02,470
and simply answer the question the first time I ask it. "

79
00:06:13,550 --> 00:06:16,670
Who does Alexander Grayson love?

80
00:06:20,330 --> 00:06:21,990
Oh, well.

81
00:06:23,390 --> 00:06:24,810
Perhaps next time.

